I came here yesterday night, and the atmosphere was amazing.  The lighting was neon, but not too gaudy, and still cozy.  After sitting down, we were given warm towelettes for our hands.  The menu was extensive, and I ordered the yellow curry chicken.  Presentation of the dish was great as well.  The curry itself was very flavorful and full of generous chicken pieces.  The meal ended with artfully sliced oranges.  There is a backyard seating option, but last night was rather chilly, so we didn't go for that option.  The staff was very attentive and polite.  The napkins were also very nice.  I came here again for the red curry chicken and it was delicious!  Again, the staff was great.  I visited this place again for the yellow curry chicken.  This time, I ordered the dish with just eggplant as the vegetable, which is what I will be doing from now on (I am not the biggest fan of vegetables).  The portions and dining experience are excellent, especially for the price.  I love this place and will be coming back again soon.  After my fourth time here, I realized that this is one of the only places that I will eat vegetables from.  I tried the crispy calamari, and it went well with the Thai chili sauce that it came with.  The calamari came on top of a pile of spinach and other leafy vegetables that had 2 dressings on them.  As always, the curry chicken was amazing.  I came here for Valentine's Day at around 9:30 and it was surprisingly pretty empty.  Everything was amazing as always.  For the holiday, we were given a box of Lindt chocolates as a gift after our meal.  It was a nice touch that I didn't expect.  Came here yet again, and ask to sit outside during the summer!  It's probably less crowded (not that being crowded is really a problem here), and it's a nice atmosphere.

Saketumi had a very extensive menu covering dishes from Japan, Malaysia and Thailand. There is surely something that even the pickiest of eaters will find. I ordered from the sushi menu and found that the rolls were made pretty well with the rice and filling ratio. The rolls didn't necessarily blow me away but they were better than your standard sushi takeout spots. Servers were very attentive and friendly. One of the ladies chatted with us for a bit and you can tell her demeanor is what helps to bring many of the regular customers back. This spot is worth giving a try if you're in Brooklyn Heights and can't really figure out what to eat as there are so many options here.
